            .swiper-slide.fit.bg-master-lightest
              .container
                .col-sm-6.col-sm-height.col-middle
                  p.m-b-20.text-left
                    | Chinese people love her story because she represents the prominence of Xiao or Hsiao, which means filial piety. As a young woman, Mulan decides to impersonate a man to serve in the army in the place of her father. 
                .col-sm-6.col-sm-height.col-middle.sm-text-center
                  img(alt="", src="assets/images/background/3.jpg", height="300px")
            .swiper-slide.fit.bg-master-lightest
              .container
                .col-sm-4.col-sm-height.col-middle.sm-text-center
                  img(alt="", src="assets/images/background/4.jpg", height="300px")
                .col-sm-8.col-sm-height.col-middle
                  p.m-b-20.text-left
                    | There was a 1998 movie version of Mulan made by Disney studios, which has influenced children worldwide. The animated English-speaking speaker, Mulan fully illustrates the Chinese culture to the western world; therefore, other fascinating topics arise. Western people evaluate Mulan extremely differently from people from to East. People think that she is the new modern female hero because she subverts traditional female status in society. The image that she created is the powerful and independent warrior, and no more cowardly wives or slaves, as well as the capable housewife who traditionally sits beside her husband all the time. In this project, the designer redesigned the image of the character at three different time periods, which are called Hua Dan, Wu Jing, and Tsing Yi.
